ZH: 我们的掌心是我们身体最敏感的部位。
EN: The palms of our hands are the most sensitive parts of our body.

ZH: 她用掌心轻轻触摸了他的脸颊。
EN: She gently touched his cheek with the palm of her hand.

ZH: 小猫用掌心试探地拨弄了纱帽。
EN: The kitten tentatively toyed with the sun hat using its paw.

ZH: 她在掌心写下了一段情话。
EN: She wrote a love message in the palm of her hand.

ZH: 他展示了自己掌心上的纹身。
EN: He displayed the tattoo on his palm.

ZH: 我的手心被冷风吹得冰凉。
EN: The cold wind made my palm freezing.

ZH: 母亲把中国地图藏在她的掌心里。
EN: Mother hid the map of China in the palm of her hand.

ZH: 他把一枚硬币藏在了掌心里。
EN: He hid a coin in the palm of his hand.

ZH: 我在掌心上画了一个笑脸。
EN: I drew a smiley face on the palm of my hand.

ZH: 他的掌心上有一颗痣。
EN: He has a birthmark on the palm of his hand.

ZH: 她紧握拳头，以避免展示掌心上的伤痕。
EN: She clenched her fist to avoid showing the scars on the palm of her hand.

ZH: 在掌心上按摩穴位可以缓解压力。
EN: Massaging the acupoints on the palm can relieve stress.

ZH: 他试图读出掌心纹路的含义。
EN: He tried to interpret the meaning of the palm lines.

ZH: 他们牵着彼此的手掌心，走过了无数的风雨。
EN: They held each other's palms and walked through countless storms.

ZH: 听着音乐，她随着节奏摆动着掌心。
EN: Listening to the music, she swayed her palms to the rhythm.

ZH: 那位艺术家用手掌心完成了一幅精美的油画。
EN: The artist completed a beautiful oil painting using the palm of his hand.

ZH: 他亲吻了她的掌心，表示深深的爱意。
EN: He kissed her palm to express his deep love.

ZH: 大象用鼻子触摸着太阳暴露在掌心的皮肤。
EN: The elephant touched the exposed skin on the palm with its trunk.

ZH: 她用掌心捧起一朵鲜花，温柔地闻了闻。
EN: She cupped a flower in her palm and gently smelled it.

ZH: 教练教会了我如何平衡掌心上的乒乓球。
EN: The coach taught me how to balance a ping pong ball on the palm of my hand.

ZH: 他把燃烧的蜡烛放在平摊的掌心上。
EN: He placed the burning candle on the flat palm of his hand.
